He who declares to man what his thought is
Lord, You render to each one according to his work

God has spoken that power belongs to God

Abba, Father all things are possible for You

The earth is full of Your possessions
Lord, You knew the face of the earth
Lord, You visit the earth and water it
You greatly enrich it through the river of God full of water
You bless its growth
The earth is full of the goodness of the Lord
He who has set all the borders of the earth
The Creator of the ends of the earth
He who builds His layers in the sky, and has founded His strata in the earth
He who established the world firmly

The number of Your years cannot be discovered
You crown the year with Your goodness
Your paths drip with fatness
With You is the fountain of life
Your judgements are a great deep
Your thoughts are very deep
Oh, the depth of the riches both of the wisdom and knowledge of God
Your greatness is un-searchable
You do great things past finding and wonders without numbers
He who breaks in pieces mighty men without inquiry and sets others in their place
There is no searching of Your understanding
Your paths are past finding out
O! Lord, how great are Your works
Your work is perfect and all Your ways are justice
Your righteousness is like the great mountains
Your glory is the earth and heaven
He who said, I am with you always, even to the end of the age
For Your mercy, O Lord which is in the heavens
Your faithfulness reaches to the clouds
The children of men take refuge under the shadow of Your wings
For the chariots of God that are twenty thousand even thousands of thousands
He who makes the clouds His chariot and walks on wings
He who rides on the clouds
Lord, You have stretched out the heavens like a curtain
He who counts the number of the stars and calls them all by name
He who seals off the stars
The Lord who knows how to deliver the godly out of temptations
He who knows to reserve the unjust under punishment for the day of judgement
God who is greater than our heart, and knows all things
Lord, You are greater than Jonah
You are greater than Solomon
You are greater than all
You are greater than the temple
The Lord is great in Zion
He who is in us is greater than he who is in the world
Your understanding is infinite
Great is Your goodness
Great is Your beauty
Great is Your faithfulness
Your mercies are very great
Great is the glory of my Lord
Your mercy toward me is great
Lord, You command Your loving kindness in the day time
Your loving kindness is better than life
The Lord who gives grace and glory
How precious is Your loving kindness O!, God
Your mercy endures for ever
It is Your mercies that we are not consumed
Your mercies are new every morning
The Lord who crowns me with loving kindness and tender mercies
For Your compassions that fail not
For all Your benefits
Lord, You are clothed with honour and majesty
You are girded with strength
You cover Yourself with light as with a garments
He who put on righteousness as a breast plate
He who put on a helmet of salvation on His head
He who put on the garments of vengeance for clothing
He who is glad with zeal as a cloak
He who has the sharp two-edged sword
He who makes His angels, Spirits
Lord, You satisfy the longing soul
You fill the hungry soul with goodness
He who sends His word and heals
For Your word which gives me comfort in my afflictions
For the wondrous things from Your Law (Bible)
Lord, You have caused me to hope upon Your Word
For Your Word which gives me life
You have dealt well (are dealing well, will deal well) with Your servants
Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path
Your words give light and understanding to the simple
For Your words which is very pure and tried
Your word was to me joy and rejoicing of my heart
Your words do good to him who walks uprightly
Your words are faithful and worthy of all acceptance
O! God, Your word is living and powerful
Your word is like a fire and like a hammer that breaks the rock in pieces
He who makes His words fire
The word of the Lord is right, and all His work is done in truth
Your commandment is exceedingly broad
Lord, You did, and You will do awesome deeds to us
Lord, in righteousness You will answer
Lord, Your anger is but for a moment, but Your favour is for a life time
Lord, You will not keep Your anger for ever
There is forgiveness with You
With You is abundant redemption
For the help of Your countenance
The Lord who made the heavens
He who made the worlds
He who made the sea into dry land
You broke open the fountain and the flood
You dried up mighty rivers
In the day time, You let Your people with the cloud and all the night with a light of fire
He who split the rocks in the wilderness and gave them drink
The waters of Marah were made sweet by You O! Lord
He who sent the bread of the angels as food in abundance
He who broke the wall of Jericho
He who opened the mouth of the donkey to speak
You made the Sun stand still over Gibeon and Moon in the valley of Aijalon
He who makes the morning darkness
He who turns the rivers into a wilderness
He who turns the water into dry ground
You turn the wilderness into pools of water
Lord, You turn the rock into a pool of water
You turn the dry land into water springs
He who brings the time of birth and he who causes delivery
The Lord who rebuilt the ruined places
Lord, You will seek what was lost
You bring back what was driven away
You will bind up the broken
You are a hiding place from the wind and a cover from the tempest
You will make darkness light before them and crooked place straight
